      "content": "Lactic acid buildup can cause the sensation of burning or cramping due to its role in reducing the pH levels in your muscles. Lower pH levels can disrupt the function of metabolic enzymes and interfere with muscle contraction, leading to the uncomfortable sensations. Additionally, the pain may also be due to the muscle fibers' inability to sustain their contractions effectively under the lower pH conditions, causing a temporary reduction in muscle performance and discomfort. Over time, the body adapts to handle lactic acid more efficiently, reducing its impact on muscle endurance.",
